We need to find the least natural number $n \geq 3$ such that all colorings of $n$ points are "good". A coloring is good if there exist three points $A_i, A_j, A_{2j-i}$, where $1 \leq i < 2j-i \leq n$, which are colored the same color.

First, let's think about how to approach this problem. We need to determine the minimum $n \geq 3$ such that any 2-coloring of the points $A_1, A_2, \ldots, A_n$ contains a monochromatic triple $A_i, A_j, A_{2j-i}$ with $1 \leq i < 2j-i \leq n$.

